Package: pixel-gl
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, tcl8.4, pixel-core (>= 3.1.0), libgl1-mesa-glx
Description: OpenGL wrapper for the Pixel framework
 Pixel is a Tcl extension that provides low level raster graphics functions,
 and through the use of helper modules allows loading and saving a large
 number of image formats, rendering True Type fonts, applying graphics filters
 and displaying to various targets, like SDL, Tk images, and so forth
 .
 This package implements a thin wrapper on top of the OpenGL library.  You
 probably will also need Pixel_sdl (which supports OpenGL rendering to its
 surfaces) or Pixel_tkgl (which allows OpenGL rendering to a Tk widget)
